  "text": "In optics, the HGFs are the solutions of the paraxial equation in Cartesian coordinates [CITATION_1] . The complete solution is not discussed here due to lots of beam parameters w(z), q(z) and the phase term P (z). We focus ourselves on the solutions at the origin, i.e. z = 0, neglect the phase term, and deal with one-dimensional solutions. The simplest solution set is the standard Hermite Gaussian functions (sHGFs), which are",
